The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 4: The United Forum of Bank Unions (UFBU) has called a work strike on June 12 to protest against low wage hikes and matters pertaining to pension options. Around 8,00,000 employees of public sector banks will go on strike. Indian Banks Association officials will meet UFBU representatives tomorrow in the presence of the chief labour commissioner to discuss all issues.                             
	 New Delhi, June 4: The Union budget is likely to be presented in Parliament on July 3.The Economic Survey is exected to be tabled in the House on July 2 and the rail budget on July 1, government sources said here tonight.                             
	 Mumbai, June 4: The MCX Stock Exchange will divest an 18 per cent stake to domestic banks. The currency futures exchange divested 6.48 per cent equity to the Union Bank of India and the Bank of India through a primary offering at Rs 10 per share amounting to Rs 87.5 crore.                             
	 New Delhi, June 4: The ministry of corporate affairs has asked Bharti Airtel to furnish details of its proposed $23-billion deal with South African telecom major MTN for legal scrutiny.                             
	 New Delhi, June 4: Inflation today declined to 0.48 per cent for the week ended May 23 from 0.61 per cent in the previous week. The rate of price rise was 8.90 per cent a year ago.                                                                                                                                      
